title: Democratic Party of Georgia
deleted: As the state has gotten more diverse with the growth of the [[Atlanta metropolitan area]], margins of victory for Republicans have significantly decreased in recent times. During the 2018 Midterm elections, Republicans lost 10 State House seats<ref>[[2018 Georgia House of Representatives election]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=June 2020}} and 2 State Senate seats.<ref>[[2018 Georgia State Senate election]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=June 2020}} Governor [[Brian Kemp]], a Republican, only won the gubernatorial race by 1.39% in 2018.<ref>[[2018 Georgia gubernatorial election#General election]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=June 2020}}, with former Republican Governor [[Nathan Deal]] clinching almost 8% of the vote just four years prior.<ref>[[2014 Georgia gubernatorial election]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=June 2020}}
